1
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:22,940
♪Only after bloom comes fruit♪

2
00:00:24,350 --> 00:00:28,320
♪Who says glory must fade to the past♪

3
00:00:30,980 --> 00:00:36,070
♪Only through thunder
do you reach the clouds♪

4
00:00:37,270 --> 00:00:42,180
♪Who made you the crown of every peak♪

5
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:46,990
♪I stand at the center of the stage♪

6
00:00:46,990 --> 00:00:50,060
♪My shadow is pinned against the wall♪

7
00:00:50,770 --> 00:00:55,720
♪Facing the light earns every medal♪

8
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:59,940
♪Little birds,
save your needless pecking♪

9
00:00:59,940 --> 00:01:03,220
♪The open sky rises high♪

10
00:01:03,760 --> 00:01:08,890
♪When night falls,
the moon begins to shine♪

11
00:01:09,660 --> 00:01:12,920
♪I stand in the heart of these lands♪

12
00:01:12,920 --> 00:01:16,280
♪My shadow bears no crown or robe♪

13
00:01:16,690 --> 00:01:22,360
♪Then I know truth needs no disguise♪

14
00:01:22,770 --> 00:01:26,020
♪The green hills see me as I am♪

15
00:01:26,020 --> 00:01:29,350
♪Like dew, lightning,
and moon on the river♪

16
00:01:29,750 --> 00:01:33,790
♪Showing me exactly who I am♪

17
00:01:33,790 --> 00:01:35,040
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,067 --> 00:01:37,856
=Episode 41=

19
00:01:38,944 --> 00:01:39,776
Let me tell you.

20
00:01:39,776 --> 00:01:42,335
It's been ages since
we've seen such a grand spectacle.

21
00:01:42,335 --> 00:01:42,936
Exactly.

22
00:01:42,936 --> 00:01:43,696
That's right.

23
00:01:44,016 --> 00:01:45,455
We really ought to thank Ms. Yi

24
00:01:45,455 --> 00:01:46,416
giving us opportunities.

25
00:01:46,416 --> 00:01:47,095
Right?

26
00:01:47,095 --> 00:01:48,776
You're right about that.

27
00:01:48,776 --> 00:01:50,735
We truly need to thank Qin'e.

28
00:01:50,735 --> 00:01:51,264
Qin'e.

29
00:01:51,576 --> 00:01:54,416
This shows there are still people
enjoying Qinqiang opera.

30
00:01:54,416 --> 00:01:55,056
Exactly.

31
00:01:55,056 --> 00:01:55,576
Exactly.

32
00:01:56,656 --> 00:01:57,216
Really.

33
00:01:57,895 --> 00:01:59,615
We should also thank Sanyuan.

34
00:01:59,776 --> 00:02:00,776
His drumming was superb.

35
00:02:01,095 --> 00:02:02,815
He played the very soul out of it.

36
00:02:02,815 --> 00:02:03,615
Exactly.

37
00:02:03,615 --> 00:02:05,095
Mr. Hu's drumming skills

38
00:02:05,535 --> 00:02:07,455
are worthy of a solo performance.

39
00:02:07,455 --> 00:02:08,215
Right?

40
00:02:08,215 --> 00:02:09,735
That's just too much, you!

41
00:02:10,136 --> 00:02:11,455
This is nothing.

42
00:02:11,455 --> 00:02:12,655
Today,

43
00:02:12,895 --> 00:02:15,816
listening to his drum performance
is truly an artistic delight.

44
00:02:15,816 --> 00:02:16,416
Exactly.

45
00:02:16,416 --> 00:02:17,296
I'm flattered.

46
00:02:17,296 --> 00:02:18,416
I still need more practice.

47
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:20,096
Let's learn from each other.

48
00:02:20,096 --> 00:02:21,175
Why learn from me?

49
00:02:21,216 --> 00:02:22,856
You've reached the peak,
why still learn?

50
00:02:23,536 --> 00:02:24,536
There's no limit to art.

51
00:02:24,536 --> 00:02:27,016
You should learn from him.

52
00:02:27,416 --> 00:02:29,096
Actually, you'd
get tired of it over time.

53
00:02:29,895 --> 00:02:31,856
Once we reach Chang'an,
don't rush home first.

54
00:02:32,455 --> 00:02:35,296
Go with me to the Northwest Gold Store
on East Street to buy something.

55
00:02:36,096 --> 00:02:36,895
What are you buying?

56
00:02:37,576 --> 00:02:39,256
At a gold store, what else?

57
00:02:39,935 --> 00:02:40,856
Who is it for?

58
00:02:41,256 --> 00:02:42,215
For Hua, of course.

59
00:02:44,576 --> 00:02:45,816
You're buying a ring?

60
00:02:47,455 --> 00:02:49,175
Uncle, you've finally
come to your senses?

61
00:02:49,816 --> 00:02:51,696
At my age, coming to my senses?

62
00:02:51,696 --> 00:02:52,864
I figured it out long ago.

63
00:02:52,864 --> 00:02:54,048
Just waiting for the moment.

64
00:02:54,256 --> 00:02:55,055
Now it's the moment.

65
00:02:55,376 --> 00:02:56,455
How do you know that?

66
00:02:57,136 --> 00:02:58,895
It's a secret, can't tell.

67
00:02:59,816 --> 00:03:00,935
All you know is this.

68
00:03:00,935 --> 00:03:02,136
Look at the drumsticks.

69
00:03:23,256 --> 00:03:33,136
♪My dear son pleads to go to war♪

70
00:03:35,455 --> 00:03:38,016
♪You'll head to battle with your skills♪

71
00:03:38,016 --> 00:03:40,656
♪I'm not worried♪

72
00:03:41,504 --> 00:03:42,976
Who's my dear son?

73
00:03:44,055 --> 00:03:45,455
Are you my dear son?

74
00:03:51,175 --> 00:03:52,136
You're back.

75
00:03:52,935 --> 00:03:54,016
Did it go well?

76
00:03:57,655 --> 00:03:58,256
Very well.

77
00:03:58,856 --> 00:04:01,096
My performance this time
was a huge success.

78
00:04:01,576 --> 00:04:05,256
As soon as I stepped on stage,
I felt energized again.

79
00:04:05,792 --> 00:04:07,376
I should get back on stage earlier.

80
00:04:09,655 --> 00:04:13,455
Next, I'll refine my performance.

81
00:04:15,935 --> 00:04:16,576
Look.

82
00:04:17,136 --> 00:04:19,016
I put on makeup today. Do I look good?

83
00:04:31,424 --> 00:04:32,056
So beautiful.

84
00:04:37,095 --> 00:04:38,056
The kid's still here.

85
00:04:40,455 --> 00:04:41,855
He's still little, knows nothing.

86
00:04:45,056 --> 00:04:46,095
Mom will be back soon.

87
00:04:46,696 --> 00:04:48,975
Let's seize time before she's back.

88
00:04:51,455 --> 00:04:52,256
What's wrong?

89
00:04:54,576 --> 00:04:56,376
We're legally married.

90
00:04:57,616 --> 00:04:59,895
You're my wife, and I'm your husband.
What's the problem?

91
00:05:00,496 --> 00:05:01,616
This isn't against the law.

92
00:05:02,736 --> 00:05:03,576
Are you crazy?

93
00:05:04,016 --> 00:05:05,095
How come?

94
00:05:05,775 --> 00:05:07,256
This is normal married life.

95
00:05:07,256 --> 00:05:08,895
I'm wearing my Mu Guiying costume.

96
00:05:10,215 --> 00:05:11,455
I love seeing you in costume.

97
00:05:13,056 --> 00:05:14,736
You insane!

98
00:05:17,576 --> 00:05:18,215
What's wrong?

99
00:05:18,496 --> 00:05:21,576
On stage, you're passionately in love
with others. Why not with me?

100
00:05:21,576 --> 00:05:23,655
You act so convincingly.
Why are you avoiding?

101
00:05:23,655 --> 00:05:25,056
Today, I have to sleep with you.

102
00:05:26,696 --> 00:05:27,816
Are you insane?

103
00:05:33,775 --> 00:05:35,215
Which one of us is insane, Yi Qin'e?

104
00:05:37,616 --> 00:05:39,016
You're like a monster.

105
00:06:02,895 --> 00:06:04,136
I am a monster.

106
00:06:07,655 --> 00:06:08,775
Still want to sleep with me?

107
00:06:21,775 --> 00:06:23,016
(Liu Hongbing is furious)

108
00:06:23,455 --> 00:06:25,565
(because he sees Yi Qin'e)

109
00:06:25,565 --> 00:06:28,136
(as the only light in his life.)

110
00:06:29,176 --> 00:06:32,335
(But that light only shines on stage.)

111
00:06:33,376 --> 00:06:35,455
(Yi Qin'e is enraged)

112
00:06:35,576 --> 00:06:37,176
(because she thinks Liu Hongbing)

113
00:06:37,295 --> 00:06:39,016
(desecrated Mu Guiying.)

114
00:06:39,576 --> 00:06:40,415
(He doesn't know)

115
00:06:40,415 --> 00:06:44,176
(the place Mu Guiying holds
in Yi Qin'e's heart.)

116
00:06:45,256 --> 00:06:48,895
(But neither speaks their mind.)

117
00:07:01,561 --> 00:07:03,066
(Chang'an Youth Palace)

118
00:07:03,136 --> 00:07:09,120
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

119
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:15,136
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

120
00:07:15,136 --> 00:07:21,376
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

121
00:07:21,376 --> 00:07:27,696
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

122
00:07:27,696 --> 00:07:33,616
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

123
00:07:34,095 --> 00:07:36,256
Okay, everyone, take a break.

124
00:07:36,256 --> 00:07:37,376
Have some water.

125
00:07:42,456 --> 00:07:43,016
How's it?

126
00:07:43,576 --> 00:07:45,295
You look so beautiful in that costume.

127
00:07:46,256 --> 00:07:47,095
Did it go well?

128
00:07:47,415 --> 00:07:48,456
Very well.

129
00:07:48,936 --> 00:07:50,775
You're just sugarcoating the bad news.

130
00:07:52,175 --> 00:07:54,016
Nowadays, kids in trainee classes

131
00:07:54,016 --> 00:07:56,496
are all signing up
for piano or dance lessons.

132
00:07:56,496 --> 00:07:58,215
Who still watches Qinqiang opera?

133
00:07:58,696 --> 00:07:59,346
Well,

134
00:07:59,346 --> 00:08:00,855
this time, it really went well.

135
00:08:02,095 --> 00:08:04,056
Qin'e makes a difference
once she's on stage.

136
00:08:04,696 --> 00:08:06,335
It feels like going back
to the old days.

137
00:08:06,896 --> 00:08:07,535
Really?

138
00:08:07,775 --> 00:08:08,855
Why would I lie to you?

139
00:08:09,335 --> 00:08:11,256
She herself feels so motivated.

140
00:08:11,535 --> 00:08:14,456
We've already set the time
for the next booking and everything.

141
00:08:15,335 --> 00:08:16,936
That's really great.

142
00:08:18,056 --> 00:08:19,816
When should I go see her and the kid?

143
00:08:20,655 --> 00:08:21,496
How about today?

144
00:08:22,975 --> 00:08:23,576
Well,

145
00:08:24,696 --> 00:08:26,496
I have something serious to tell you.

146
00:08:27,456 --> 00:08:29,056
You've been playful for half your life.

147
00:08:29,056 --> 00:08:30,696
What serious thing could you have?

148
00:08:37,136 --> 00:08:37,856
Where's the thing?

149
00:08:38,935 --> 00:08:39,736
What's wrong?

150
00:08:41,775 --> 00:08:43,616
I put that thing in Qin'e's bag.

151
00:08:44,055 --> 00:08:45,976
When did you learn
to keep people in suspense?

152
00:08:45,976 --> 00:08:48,535
Just tell me what it is.

153
00:08:48,535 --> 00:08:49,455
No way.

154
00:08:51,096 --> 00:08:52,535
Anyway, we're going to her place.

155
00:08:53,736 --> 00:08:55,016
I'll tell you there.

156
00:08:57,535 --> 00:08:58,455
When does class end?

157
00:09:03,815 --> 00:09:06,415
Kids, how about we end class now?

158
00:09:06,415 --> 00:09:08,216
Okay!

159
00:09:08,216 --> 00:09:09,575
Why aren't you teaching seriously?

160
00:09:10,096 --> 00:09:10,896
Not your business.

161
00:09:22,655 --> 00:09:23,175
Hongbing.

162
00:09:25,055 --> 00:09:25,896
Where's Qin'e?

163
00:09:28,256 --> 00:09:29,415
She put the kid to sleep?

164
00:09:32,216 --> 00:09:32,935
What's wrong?

165
00:09:32,935 --> 00:09:33,935
What's wrong with you?

166
00:09:36,376 --> 00:09:37,775
Why being in a sulk?

167
00:09:40,376 --> 00:09:41,256
What's wrong?

168
00:09:43,216 --> 00:09:44,136
Had a fight?

169
00:09:45,655 --> 00:09:47,256
Anyway, he shouldn't treat me like this.

170
00:09:50,535 --> 00:09:51,072
This...

171
00:09:51,655 --> 00:09:52,256
What's wrong?

172
00:09:52,256 --> 00:09:53,096
What happened?

173
00:09:53,096 --> 00:09:53,935
What's this about?

174
00:09:56,376 --> 00:09:57,496
Did you fight with Hongbing?

175
00:10:01,976 --> 00:10:02,856
Where's the kid?

176
00:10:03,455 --> 00:10:04,935
Wait, you had a fight, right?

177
00:10:08,736 --> 00:10:09,496
Sanyuan.

178
00:10:10,175 --> 00:10:11,455
Come see the kid.

179
00:10:11,455 --> 00:10:11,968
What's it?

180
00:10:12,415 --> 00:10:12,928
This...

181
00:10:13,336 --> 00:10:14,736
Why is his face all purple?

182
00:10:15,535 --> 00:10:16,256
Laidi.

183
00:10:16,256 --> 00:10:16,775
Laidi.

184
00:10:16,775 --> 00:10:17,336
Laidi.

185
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:18,256
What's wrong?

186
00:10:18,256 --> 00:10:19,175
What's wrong?

187
00:10:23,455 --> 00:10:24,175
How is it?

188
00:10:24,175 --> 00:10:24,856
Losing again.

189
00:10:26,136 --> 00:10:26,775
Hongbing.

190
00:10:27,935 --> 00:10:30,136
What an unusual day.

191
00:10:30,616 --> 00:10:32,175
Didn't you go straight?

192
00:10:32,935 --> 00:10:34,336
Why are you coming to us now?

193
00:10:34,736 --> 00:10:36,016
What did you say?

194
00:10:36,815 --> 00:10:37,415
Hongbing.

195
00:10:38,136 --> 00:10:39,136
Didn't you say?

196
00:10:39,616 --> 00:10:41,055
Don't even mention girls,

197
00:10:41,496 --> 00:10:44,856
even if the Jade Emperor's sister came,
you wouldn't be interested.

198
00:10:46,376 --> 00:10:47,616
Why are you here with us?

199
00:10:48,216 --> 00:10:49,535
Enough now.

200
00:11:10,415 --> 00:11:11,896
Why is it so quiet?

201
00:11:15,575 --> 00:11:16,455
Don't panic.

202
00:11:16,815 --> 00:11:18,976
The kid is so young,
it can't be anything serious.

203
00:11:20,976 --> 00:11:22,616
Doctor, what's wrong with my kid?

204
00:11:23,175 --> 00:11:24,775
He's stabilized now.
He lacked of oxygen.

205
00:11:25,376 --> 00:11:26,415
- Mom.
- Don't let too many people in.

206
00:11:26,415 --> 00:11:27,016
Yiyi.

207
00:11:27,616 --> 00:11:28,376
My Yiyi.

208
00:11:28,376 --> 00:11:30,216
Doctor, what's wrong with the kid?

209
00:11:30,815 --> 00:11:32,736
Some test results aren't in yet.

210
00:11:33,256 --> 00:11:35,175
But you need
to mentally prepare yourselves.

211
00:11:35,976 --> 00:11:36,736
What do you mean?

212
00:11:37,175 --> 00:11:38,415
Talk after the results are in.

213
00:11:42,496 --> 00:11:43,216
How's the kid?

214
00:11:43,775 --> 00:11:44,775
He's stabilized now.

215
00:11:44,775 --> 00:11:46,080
They said he lacked of oxygen.

216
00:11:46,376 --> 00:11:47,376
What's really going on?

217
00:11:47,775 --> 00:11:50,096
Some test results aren't in yet,
so we need to wait.

218
00:11:50,575 --> 00:11:51,815
Still haven't reached Hongbing?

219
00:11:52,736 --> 00:11:53,295
No.

220
00:11:55,096 --> 00:11:57,136
Where has he gone?

221
00:12:17,575 --> 00:12:18,175
Mom.

222
00:12:19,736 --> 00:12:20,496
Qin'e.

223
00:13:01,175 --> 00:13:02,905
The kid has Tetralogy of Fallot,

224
00:13:02,905 --> 00:13:05,376
which is a congenital heart defect.

225
00:13:10,336 --> 00:13:12,616
His heart was malformed from birth.

226
00:13:13,415 --> 00:13:15,896
He didn't develop properly in the womb.

227
00:13:16,736 --> 00:13:18,016
With ventricular septal defect,

228
00:13:18,376 --> 00:13:19,655
pulmonary stenosis,

229
00:13:20,224 --> 00:13:21,623
overriding aorta,

230
00:13:21,944 --> 00:13:24,543
and right ventricular hypertrophy.

231
00:13:25,743 --> 00:13:27,743
Is it very serious?

232
00:13:28,304 --> 00:13:30,704
It's a heart problem,
how could it not be serious?

233
00:13:31,143 --> 00:13:34,584
If the child hadn't been
resuscitated in time this time,

234
00:13:34,584 --> 00:13:35,304
he could be gone.

235
00:13:35,863 --> 00:13:38,344
This condition isn't extremely rare,

236
00:13:38,824 --> 00:13:40,863
but it is deadly.

237
00:13:41,224 --> 00:13:42,464
Be mentally prepared.

238
00:13:43,184 --> 00:13:46,344
Fifty percent of patients
don't live past three years old.

239
00:13:46,984 --> 00:13:49,383
Seventy percent don't make it to ten.

240
00:13:50,623 --> 00:13:51,984
Ninety percent

241
00:13:52,783 --> 00:13:53,584
will die young.

242
00:13:56,104 --> 00:13:57,783
What have we done wrong?

243
00:13:58,543 --> 00:14:00,663
Why does the child suffer this?

244
00:14:03,464 --> 00:14:05,184
Mom, maybe you all go wait outside.

245
00:14:05,783 --> 00:14:07,543
Stop crying here, go outside.

246
00:14:07,704 --> 00:14:09,184
L-Let's go out.

247
00:14:09,184 --> 00:14:10,984
Let the doctor talk properly with Qin'e.

248
00:14:13,344 --> 00:14:15,224
I thought there's something
wrong with him.

249
00:14:15,584 --> 00:14:17,704
Even a little movement
and he'd be panting.

250
00:14:17,863 --> 00:14:18,663
Don't rush, sit.

251
00:14:18,663 --> 00:14:20,064
His face would be so red.

252
00:14:21,023 --> 00:14:21,663
Besides,

253
00:14:22,143 --> 00:14:23,184
other babies

254
00:14:23,520 --> 00:14:24,903
lift their heads at two months,

255
00:14:24,903 --> 00:14:26,304
roll over at three months,

256
00:14:26,304 --> 00:14:27,783
and can sit at six months.

257
00:14:28,344 --> 00:14:30,863
Yet our child couldn't do any of that.

258
00:14:31,143 --> 00:14:33,224
What's the use
of rambling about this now?

259
00:14:36,903 --> 00:14:37,944
Where have you been?

260
00:14:38,783 --> 00:14:40,224
Didn't even reply to the message.

261
00:14:40,224 --> 00:14:42,184
How many pages did I send you?

262
00:14:43,543 --> 00:14:44,304
Where's Qin'e?

263
00:14:44,824 --> 00:14:45,543
Inside.

264
00:14:50,023 --> 00:14:52,304
We've never had

265
00:14:52,783 --> 00:14:55,903
a successful precedent for performing
heart surgery on a child here.

266
00:14:57,023 --> 00:14:58,143
So...

267
00:14:58,143 --> 00:14:59,863
That means there's no cure.

268
00:15:00,704 --> 00:15:01,464
For now.

269
00:15:03,143 --> 00:15:04,783
But, you must have hope.

270
00:15:05,464 --> 00:15:07,383
After all, the child is still young.

271
00:15:08,224 --> 00:15:09,903
Technology has advanced rapidly.

272
00:15:10,503 --> 00:15:12,623
Perhaps there will be a cure next year.

273
00:15:12,623 --> 00:15:14,023
Then what do we do now?

274
00:15:14,424 --> 00:15:15,104
Hang in there.

275
00:15:16,424 --> 00:15:18,704
Observe him closely.

276
00:15:19,704 --> 00:15:22,304
If you notice his face turning red,

277
00:15:22,663 --> 00:15:25,143
or cyanosis appears,
seek medical help immediately.

278
00:15:25,783 --> 00:15:27,704
The child's condition is stable for now.

279
00:15:28,344 --> 00:15:29,663
I'll prescribe some medication.

280
00:15:30,064 --> 00:15:31,064
You can go home then.

281
00:15:48,944 --> 00:15:51,263
Qin'e, let me hold the child.

282
00:15:53,623 --> 00:15:54,263
Qin'e.

283
00:16:16,464 --> 00:16:17,304
Doctor,

284
00:16:18,304 --> 00:16:20,704
why didn't our child develop properly?

285
00:16:21,143 --> 00:16:22,143
Many possible causes.

286
00:16:22,783 --> 00:16:25,224
Like smoking or drinking,

287
00:16:25,224 --> 00:16:27,023
they could cause
congenital malformations.

288
00:16:27,424 --> 00:16:30,903
Did you take any medicine
during your pregnancy?

289
00:16:32,584 --> 00:16:35,584
Genetic mutations,
environmental factors,

290
00:16:35,584 --> 00:16:36,984
anything is possible.

291
00:16:39,143 --> 00:16:40,184
Give me the kid.

292
00:16:40,984 --> 00:16:42,104
You go inside and rest.

293
00:17:07,303 --> 00:17:08,343
I'll go buy something.

294
00:17:42,384 --> 00:17:44,424
(Yi Qin'e simply couldn't figure out)

295
00:17:45,184 --> 00:17:47,384
(why this happened.)

296
00:17:47,984 --> 00:17:50,743
(Perhaps heaven really
granted her too much.)

297
00:17:50,944 --> 00:17:54,424
(And now it is taking
them back bit by bit.)

298
00:17:55,743 --> 00:17:59,503
(Yi Qin'e feels
all of this was her fault.)

299
00:18:38,664 --> 00:18:40,944
No need to check.
Everyone's is the same.

300
00:18:46,023 --> 00:18:47,424
Sign it properly.

301
00:18:48,904 --> 00:18:49,823
What's wrong?

302
00:18:50,103 --> 00:18:51,023
Sign it.

303
00:18:54,783 --> 00:18:55,743
There you go.

304
00:18:56,224 --> 00:18:58,224
As expected of someone
taught by the old leader.

305
00:18:58,583 --> 00:18:59,624
You know the greater good

306
00:19:00,023 --> 00:19:01,144
and the bigger picture.

307
00:19:04,144 --> 00:19:04,664
Signed.

308
00:19:06,224 --> 00:19:08,464
Liu, don't blame me.

309
00:19:08,823 --> 00:19:10,743
This wasn't up to me either.

310
00:19:11,144 --> 00:19:13,704
The nation must develop,
and human must progress.

311
00:19:13,864 --> 00:19:16,464
See how well this calligraphy
written by the old leader is.

312
00:19:16,823 --> 00:19:18,343
But times have changed now.

313
00:19:19,144 --> 00:19:21,664
We must keep up with the times too.

314
00:19:22,144 --> 00:19:23,424
Toss the calligraphy.

315
00:19:24,543 --> 00:19:25,664
It's so ironic.

316
00:19:28,103 --> 00:19:29,904
What a lowly vulgar.

317
00:19:30,736 --> 00:19:34,048
(Never forget who dug the well.)

318
00:19:37,224 --> 00:19:38,184
Gently.

319
00:19:42,063 --> 00:19:43,303
Mom's got our child asleep?

320
00:19:49,783 --> 00:19:50,503
Let's eat first.

321
00:19:51,503 --> 00:19:52,503
I'm not eating.

322
00:19:53,823 --> 00:19:56,743
At times like this,
you should eat properly.

323
00:19:57,343 --> 00:19:58,823
We can't break down, got it?

324
00:19:59,464 --> 00:19:59,984
Come on.

325
00:20:07,343 --> 00:20:08,384
You go ahead and eat.

326
00:20:15,704 --> 00:20:16,543
What are you doing?

327
00:20:20,664 --> 00:20:21,503
I've decided

328
00:20:22,543 --> 00:20:23,384
we can't give up.

329
00:20:24,704 --> 00:20:27,063
We're taking our child
to Beijing, to Shanghai.

330
00:20:27,743 --> 00:20:28,743
To other hospitals,

331
00:20:29,263 --> 00:20:31,384
one injection might fix it.

332
00:20:31,783 --> 00:20:32,904
I bought the train tickets.

333
00:20:33,743 --> 00:20:34,783
We'll leave tomorrow.

334
00:20:35,864 --> 00:20:38,688
Beijing has Children's Hospital
and the Pediatric Research Institute.

335
00:20:41,664 --> 00:20:42,664
Then I'll go pack.

336
00:20:44,303 --> 00:20:46,263
- What?
- It's so late now.

337
00:20:46,263 --> 00:20:47,343
The kid is asleep.

338
00:20:47,783 --> 00:20:48,384
Eat first.

339
00:20:53,303 --> 00:20:54,864
Do we have enough money?

340
00:20:54,864 --> 00:20:56,424
If not, I'll borrow some from Uncle.

341
00:20:56,944 --> 00:20:59,144
Don't worry about trivial things.

342
00:20:59,144 --> 00:21:00,224
I'll handle it.

343
00:21:00,743 --> 00:21:03,103
I promise you I'll get our child cured.

344
00:21:20,023 --> 00:21:21,904
Melon seeds, peanuts,
mineral water for sale.

345
00:21:46,503 --> 00:21:47,023
Officer.

346
00:21:47,424 --> 00:21:47,984
Officer.

347
00:21:48,543 --> 00:21:51,063
Could you please check
if there are any sleeper tickets left?

348
00:21:51,384 --> 00:21:52,103
No tickets.

349
00:21:52,904 --> 00:21:54,583
We're taking our child for treatment.

350
00:21:54,583 --> 00:21:55,783
We're pressed for time.

351
00:21:55,783 --> 00:21:58,303
Your old section Chief Deng is my buddy.

352
00:21:58,303 --> 00:21:59,503
Could you make an exception?

353
00:21:59,503 --> 00:22:00,904
I said no tickets.

354
00:22:02,224 --> 00:22:03,263
That's tough.

355
00:22:06,904 --> 00:22:07,583
How's it?

356
00:22:19,503 --> 00:22:21,944
Happy birthday!

357
00:22:26,984 --> 00:22:27,864
Xiao.

358
00:22:28,184 --> 00:22:29,624
- Come on!
- Come on!

359
00:22:29,904 --> 00:22:30,743
You guys cut it.

360
00:22:32,503 --> 00:22:33,904
He's afraid I'll eat him.

361
00:22:35,864 --> 00:22:37,424
- Alright, make a wish!
- Make a wish!

362
00:22:41,263 --> 00:22:42,063
Jiahe!

363
00:22:42,063 --> 00:22:43,864
Happy birthday!

364
00:22:46,023 --> 00:22:49,184
Cheng, we're closed already.
What brings you here?

365
00:22:49,184 --> 00:22:51,303
I thought we are close friends.

366
00:22:51,303 --> 00:22:53,224
Didn't you even tell me
about your birthday?

367
00:22:53,224 --> 00:22:54,944
You're such a busy guy.

368
00:22:55,823 --> 00:22:57,424
Just a little gift.

369
00:22:57,424 --> 00:22:58,624
A money bouquet for you.

370
00:22:59,103 --> 00:23:01,704
- Wish you'll always have money!
- Good.

371
00:23:01,704 --> 00:23:02,704
Here, take it.

372
00:23:02,944 --> 00:23:03,664
Thank you.

373
00:23:03,664 --> 00:23:04,624
Thank you, Cheng.

374
00:23:04,944 --> 00:23:07,263
But this is too expensive to accept.

375
00:23:07,263 --> 00:23:09,664
This is my sincerity.

376
00:23:10,303 --> 00:23:11,424
Take it. Just take it.

377
00:23:11,424 --> 00:23:13,063
No way. I really can't take it.

378
00:23:13,503 --> 00:23:14,464
Handsome.

379
00:23:15,063 --> 00:23:16,144
You take it for her.

380
00:23:16,944 --> 00:23:18,944
I know the number of them.

381
00:23:18,944 --> 00:23:21,224
Don't worry. I won't steal it.

382
00:23:21,944 --> 00:23:22,560
Take a seat.

383
00:23:23,424 --> 00:23:25,823
Today, I've brought
a few bottles of fine wine.

384
00:23:26,944 --> 00:23:28,343
Let's have a drink.

385
00:23:29,303 --> 00:23:30,224
Sit down.

386
00:23:30,704 --> 00:23:32,743
Jiahe's friends are my friends too.

387
00:23:33,263 --> 00:23:35,144
Let's all have fun.

388
00:23:35,144 --> 00:23:36,263
- Come on, Jiahe.
- Good.

389
00:23:36,263 --> 00:23:37,184
Cheers.

390
00:23:39,184 --> 00:23:41,743
Cheng, we haven't cut the cake yet.

391
00:23:41,743 --> 00:23:43,063
And the party hasn't started.

392
00:23:43,063 --> 00:23:44,063
There's no rush.

393
00:23:46,583 --> 00:23:49,783
Every time, you always sweet-talk me.

394
00:23:49,783 --> 00:23:52,543
When we drank before,
it was always me who got drunk,

395
00:23:52,543 --> 00:23:54,704
and you never got drunk once.

396
00:23:54,704 --> 00:23:57,464
This time, I'm determined
to drink my fill with you.

397
00:23:57,823 --> 00:23:59,063
Drink until we're drunk!

398
00:23:59,063 --> 00:24:00,464
Okay, drink until we're drunk.

399
00:24:00,464 --> 00:24:01,783
Absolutely!

400
00:24:02,303 --> 00:24:03,864
I've learned a few new songs.

401
00:24:03,864 --> 00:24:05,783
I'll go sing them for you, okay?

402
00:24:07,424 --> 00:24:09,904
So you're rejecting me?

403
00:24:11,864 --> 00:24:13,464
Not at all, Cheng.

404
00:24:13,464 --> 00:24:15,224
How would I dare? Right?

405
00:24:15,904 --> 00:24:17,984
You're asking for trouble.

406
00:24:18,864 --> 00:24:21,303
I am just about to go sing for you.

407
00:24:21,704 --> 00:24:23,343
How could we reject you?

408
00:24:23,823 --> 00:24:24,343
Excuse me.

409
00:24:24,944 --> 00:24:26,063
Excuse me.

410
00:24:26,063 --> 00:24:27,984
Cheng, I toast you.

411
00:24:29,704 --> 00:24:30,464
Who are you?

412
00:24:31,023 --> 00:24:32,783
I'm a nobody.

413
00:24:34,063 --> 00:24:34,944
Cheng.

414
00:24:34,944 --> 00:24:36,023
You know it.

415
00:24:36,023 --> 00:24:37,624
Jiahe holds her liquor well.

416
00:24:38,063 --> 00:24:39,103
Boring to drink with her.

417
00:24:39,103 --> 00:24:40,184
But I can't hold my liquor.

418
00:24:40,184 --> 00:24:41,103
I'll get drunk easily.

419
00:24:41,103 --> 00:24:42,543
When I'm drunk, I'll be funny.

420
00:24:42,543 --> 00:24:43,783
Today, I'll show you.

421
00:24:43,783 --> 00:24:44,743
Allow me to toast you.

422
00:24:44,743 --> 00:24:45,464
A toast to you.

423
00:24:47,743 --> 00:24:49,303
- Listen...
- Cheng.

424
00:24:50,144 --> 00:24:52,263
You've always listened to Jiahe sing.

425
00:24:52,664 --> 00:24:53,944
But you've never heard me sing.

426
00:24:53,944 --> 00:24:55,063
I sing just as well.

427
00:24:55,464 --> 00:24:56,103
Come on.

428
00:24:56,103 --> 00:24:58,704
I'll perform Orchid Grass for Cheng.

429
00:24:58,704 --> 00:25:00,023
- Good!
- Good!

430
00:25:00,263 --> 00:25:00,864
Come on.

431
00:25:02,503 --> 00:25:05,864
Today, on Jiahe's birthday,

432
00:25:05,864 --> 00:25:08,783
I wish for the friendship
between Jiahe and Cheng

433
00:25:08,783 --> 00:25:10,103
to be like orchid grass,

434
00:25:10,103 --> 00:25:12,424
remaining pure and resilient.

435
00:25:12,424 --> 00:25:13,184
Well said!

436
00:25:13,583 --> 00:25:16,103
Forever resilient!
May our friendship last forever.

437
00:25:17,944 --> 00:25:19,823
Cheng brought fine wine today.

438
00:25:20,023 --> 00:25:21,944
No one is to spoil Cheng's fun.

439
00:25:22,583 --> 00:25:23,904
Everyone must keep him happy.

440
00:25:25,424 --> 00:25:26,384
Come on, let's drink!

441
00:25:26,503 --> 00:25:27,184
- Okay.
- Okay.

442
00:25:27,424 --> 00:25:29,144
Cheng, let me toast you.

443
00:25:32,944 --> 00:25:33,503
Cheng.

444
00:25:33,904 --> 00:25:34,743
Not enough wine.

445
00:25:35,823 --> 00:25:36,823
Go get more.

446
00:25:36,823 --> 00:25:40,823
We must keep Cheng happy today.

447
00:25:41,103 --> 00:25:41,904
- Okay.
- Okay.

448
00:25:41,904 --> 00:25:43,743
- A toast to Cheng.
- A toast to Cheng.

449
00:25:44,944 --> 00:25:47,583
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

450
00:26:30,743 --> 00:26:31,296
Here.

451
00:26:33,224 --> 00:26:34,224
Are you alright?

452
00:26:43,103 --> 00:26:44,503
Is Mr. Cheng okay?

453
00:26:45,984 --> 00:26:47,664
They carried him away.

454
00:26:50,624 --> 00:26:52,783
I've never seen him that drunk before.

455
00:27:04,704 --> 00:27:05,984
You sang

456
00:27:08,224 --> 00:27:09,384
that Orchid Grass song

457
00:27:12,103 --> 00:27:14,023
for Yi Qin'e, right?

458
00:27:22,343 --> 00:27:23,023
Right?

459
00:27:33,144 --> 00:27:35,023
What a shame.

460
00:27:36,704 --> 00:27:38,664
Such a huge birthday cake,

461
00:27:39,944 --> 00:27:42,343
I didn't get a bite of it.
I just drank the whole time.

462
00:27:46,864 --> 00:27:49,664
Didn't get a bite of it.

463
00:27:52,864 --> 00:27:54,704
Just drank the whole time.

464
00:27:55,184 --> 00:27:57,063
So you want birthday cake?

465
00:27:57,944 --> 00:27:59,063
Of course.

466
00:27:59,464 --> 00:28:00,624
Today is my birthday.

467
00:28:04,944 --> 00:28:05,543
Okay.

468
00:28:08,224 --> 00:28:09,624
You're the boss today.

469
00:28:14,823 --> 00:28:15,583
Let's go.

470
00:28:17,704 --> 00:28:18,503
Where to?

471
00:28:19,103 --> 00:28:21,103
You want birthday cake, right?

472
00:28:41,464 --> 00:28:42,343
Anyone?

473
00:28:42,823 --> 00:28:44,543
Anyone? Need to buy a birthday cake.

474
00:28:46,904 --> 00:28:48,664
Forget it, I was just saying.

475
00:28:48,944 --> 00:28:49,823
Don't be serious.

476
00:28:57,503 --> 00:28:58,343
Do you know

477
00:28:59,503 --> 00:29:01,184
where all these cars on the street

478
00:29:02,384 --> 00:29:03,664
are all heading to?

479
00:29:05,944 --> 00:29:06,664
Home.

480
00:29:12,144 --> 00:29:13,624
Among these thousands of lights,

481
00:29:18,424 --> 00:29:19,984
someday, one of them will be mine.

482
00:29:27,543 --> 00:29:28,160
Come on.

483
00:29:31,503 --> 00:29:32,144
Make a wish.

484
00:29:49,664 --> 00:29:51,343
Do you know why people make wishes?

485
00:29:54,583 --> 00:29:55,424
Because

486
00:29:57,543 --> 00:30:00,063
only after eating cake, making a wish,
and blowing out candles,

487
00:30:01,464 --> 00:30:03,023
can we get the courage for next year.

488
00:30:40,184 --> 00:30:41,224
(During this period,)

489
00:30:41,864 --> 00:30:45,543
(Yi Qin'e and Liu Hongbing travel
all over the country with their child.)

490
00:30:46,103 --> 00:30:48,263
(Whenever there's a glimmer of hope,)

491
00:30:48,823 --> 00:30:52,608
- (they'd rush over with their child.)
- Have some. It's still warm.

492
00:30:52,904 --> 00:30:55,456
- (But they always go with hope)
- I'm fine.

493
00:30:55,456 --> 00:30:57,063
(and return with disappointment.)

494
00:30:58,224 --> 00:30:59,664
(Time and again,)

495
00:31:00,184 --> 00:31:02,464
(no one could endure it any longer.)

496
00:31:16,144 --> 00:31:18,624
Hongbing, am I interrupting?

497
00:31:18,984 --> 00:31:20,303
I'll come another time.

498
00:31:20,303 --> 00:31:21,424
No, it's fine.

499
00:31:22,224 --> 00:31:23,424
Troupe Leader Shan, sit.

500
00:31:23,872 --> 00:31:25,063
Come on.

501
00:31:26,823 --> 00:31:27,384
Come on.

502
00:31:28,063 --> 00:31:28,664
Don't move.

503
00:31:29,023 --> 00:31:29,944
You messed it up.

504
00:31:30,543 --> 00:31:32,384
Sorry, Troupe Leader Shan.

505
00:31:32,823 --> 00:31:33,864
We just got back.

506
00:31:33,864 --> 00:31:36,063
We can only offer you some water.

507
00:31:36,743 --> 00:31:37,384
No problem.

508
00:31:37,384 --> 00:31:38,144
Don't mind me.

509
00:31:38,144 --> 00:31:39,144
You go ahead.

510
00:31:40,063 --> 00:31:40,904
How's the kid?

511
00:31:41,303 --> 00:31:43,384
We saw a specialist in Beijing.

512
00:31:43,664 --> 00:31:46,543
The specialist said his former student
returned from studying abroad.

513
00:31:46,543 --> 00:31:47,783
He's in Hong Kong, China now.

514
00:31:48,624 --> 00:31:50,704
It's troublesome
to go to Hong Kong, China.

515
00:31:51,063 --> 00:31:53,783
We're sorting out the paperwork
first, and then we'll go.

516
00:31:54,224 --> 00:31:55,464
When are you going?

517
00:31:55,584 --> 00:31:57,303
I'll go handle the paperwork soon.

518
00:31:57,303 --> 00:31:57,904
By the way,

519
00:31:58,303 --> 00:32:00,424
I need you to issue a certificate.

520
00:32:01,103 --> 00:32:01,904
That's easy.

521
00:32:01,904 --> 00:32:03,263
I can get it for you anytime.

522
00:32:04,144 --> 00:32:06,904
The doctor said technology has
advanced rapidly these past two years.

523
00:32:07,144 --> 00:32:09,144
In a couple of years,
there might be a cure.

524
00:32:10,664 --> 00:32:12,263
As long as the kid could be cured.

525
00:32:14,343 --> 00:32:16,424
Qin'e, I'm here

526
00:32:16,424 --> 00:32:18,424
just to tell you that Mr. Qin is here.

527
00:32:19,224 --> 00:32:20,543
Tonight,

528
00:32:20,543 --> 00:32:22,944
your uncle, Director Feng, and I

529
00:32:23,984 --> 00:32:25,904
want to host a dinner for Mr. Qin.

530
00:32:26,063 --> 00:32:28,144
I wonder if you're available

531
00:32:29,144 --> 00:32:30,063
to join us.

532
00:32:30,063 --> 00:32:31,864
Just consider it a way to relax a bit.

533
00:32:31,864 --> 00:32:34,624
Not far, at Weihua Barbecue.

534
00:32:34,823 --> 00:32:36,864
I can't go. I have
to take care of my kid.

535
00:32:37,184 --> 00:32:39,103
Troupe Leader Shan, please have a seat.

536
00:32:39,424 --> 00:32:41,664
My child needs to sleep.
I have to put her to sleep.

537
00:32:47,424 --> 00:32:48,343
Alright then.

538
00:32:48,343 --> 00:32:49,023
Take care.

539
00:32:49,023 --> 00:32:49,823
Okay.

540
00:32:50,303 --> 00:32:52,343
Are you two going
to Hong Kong, China for treatment?

541
00:32:59,424 --> 00:33:00,904
She just won't listen.

542
00:33:01,384 --> 00:33:02,864
You should try talking her out.

543
00:33:02,864 --> 00:33:04,904
You two need to talk things out.

544
00:33:04,904 --> 00:33:06,384
Keeping everything bottled up inside

545
00:33:06,384 --> 00:33:08,823
would drive you crazy.

546
00:33:09,144 --> 00:33:10,424
Don't worry.

547
00:33:10,424 --> 00:33:11,864
I'll talk to her later.

548
00:33:11,864 --> 00:33:13,224
Okay, no need to see me out.

549
00:33:13,424 --> 00:33:14,424
Bye. Take care.

550
00:33:14,424 --> 00:33:15,184
Okay.

551
00:33:16,303 --> 00:33:17,583
Not far,

552
00:33:17,583 --> 00:33:18,543
just at Weihua Barbecue.

553
00:33:18,864 --> 00:33:20,224
Come join us if you have time.

554
00:33:40,543 --> 00:33:41,303
Is the kid asleep?

555
00:33:48,256 --> 00:33:49,760
Aren't you having barbecue tonight?

556
00:33:51,103 --> 00:33:51,704
Qin'e,

557
00:33:52,624 --> 00:33:53,344
want some food?

558
00:33:53,344 --> 00:33:54,303
How about some noodles?

559
00:33:55,023 --> 00:33:55,823
Whatever.

560
00:33:59,184 --> 00:33:59,743
Qin'e.

561
00:34:01,384 --> 00:34:02,583
Can our family really afford

562
00:34:03,063 --> 00:34:05,263
to Hong Kong, China for treatment?

563
00:34:06,704 --> 00:34:08,744
The doctor just mentioned it offhand.

564
00:34:09,984 --> 00:34:11,784
He didn't say it was a guaranteed cure.

565
00:34:20,424 --> 00:34:21,703
Even if we go,

566
00:34:22,623 --> 00:34:23,543
I mean...

567
00:34:23,784 --> 00:34:26,543
Maybe we should take a break.

568
00:34:28,023 --> 00:34:29,904
Going a day or two later
won't delay anything.

569
00:34:29,904 --> 00:34:31,464
It's been almost half a year.

570
00:34:31,784 --> 00:34:32,744
You're exhausted,

571
00:34:33,663 --> 00:34:34,944
and we're out of money.

572
00:34:43,944 --> 00:34:44,544
What's wrong?

573
00:34:47,183 --> 00:34:48,663
Are you just going to watch him die?

574
00:34:52,143 --> 00:34:53,944
How can you say something like that?

575
00:34:54,143 --> 00:34:55,703
That's not what I meant.

576
00:34:55,703 --> 00:34:57,864
I'm just saying we should take a break

577
00:34:58,384 --> 00:34:59,784
and save up some money.

578
00:35:00,864 --> 00:35:02,223
Moreover, I'm exhausted too.

579
00:35:03,183 --> 00:35:04,023
You're exhausted?

580
00:35:05,424 --> 00:35:07,744
Remember that lousy
basement hotel in Beijing?

581
00:35:08,064 --> 00:35:10,112
Our child cried nonstop,
wouldn't sleep all night.

582
00:35:10,112 --> 00:35:12,384
When others annoyed,
and the owner wanted to kick us out,

583
00:35:12,384 --> 00:35:14,368
who was the one
holding him outside all night?

584
00:35:15,864 --> 00:35:17,063
Did I complain anything?

585
00:35:25,864 --> 00:35:26,464
Fine.

586
00:35:27,023 --> 00:35:28,424
You can just leave us.

587
00:35:47,984 --> 00:35:49,023
What did you say?

588
00:35:50,103 --> 00:35:51,464
How can I leave you?

589
00:35:52,904 --> 00:35:54,824
We've been fighting
for the past six months.

590
00:35:56,143 --> 00:35:57,784
Just stop. I'm sick of it.

591
00:36:00,224 --> 00:36:02,272
I didn't mean we aren't
going to Hong Kong, China.

592
00:36:03,864 --> 00:36:06,023
But given our current situation,

593
00:36:06,984 --> 00:36:09,223
we really can't go
to Hong Kong, China right now.

594
00:36:09,583 --> 00:36:10,824
We have to go, anyway.

595
00:36:18,744 --> 00:36:20,143
Can you be realistic?

596
00:36:22,384 --> 00:36:24,223
You're an out-of-work actress.

597
00:36:24,223 --> 00:36:25,663
And I'm an out-of-work driver.

598
00:36:25,663 --> 00:36:27,424
How can we afford treatment there?

599
00:36:31,063 --> 00:36:32,063
Say that again.

600
00:36:35,784 --> 00:36:37,384
I have to get treatment for my son.

601
00:36:48,543 --> 00:36:49,264
You're insane.

602
00:36:50,543 --> 00:36:51,663
Completely insane.

603
00:36:57,264 --> 00:36:58,744
Look at you.

604
00:37:00,464 --> 00:37:02,183
Still remember who you used to be?

605
00:37:04,304 --> 00:37:06,223
If you despise me, why did you marry me?

606
00:37:06,904 --> 00:37:08,063
I shouldn't have married you

607
00:37:08,063 --> 00:37:09,264
and had this child.

608
00:37:20,304 --> 00:37:23,223
In the past, if you ever
said something like that,

609
00:37:24,984 --> 00:37:26,663
it would break my heart.

610
00:37:30,344 --> 00:37:31,503
It's strange.

611
00:37:34,543 --> 00:37:35,703
I feel nothing.

612
00:37:53,623 --> 00:37:54,663
Nothing in my heart now.

613
00:38:09,904 --> 00:38:13,344
(Yi Qin'e doesn't know
why she said something like that.)

614
00:38:14,063 --> 00:38:16,503
(She just thinks she's truly gone mad.)

615
00:38:17,384 --> 00:38:20,904
(Her life, just like the Qinqiang opera
she performed on stage,)

616
00:38:21,264 --> 00:38:22,543
(in just a few years,)

617
00:38:22,904 --> 00:38:24,944
(had been thrown from its highest peak)

618
00:38:24,944 --> 00:38:26,944
(straight down
to the lowest valley by fate.)

619
00:38:27,864 --> 00:38:29,344
(Taking the kid to see the doctor.)

620
00:38:29,984 --> 00:38:32,604
(If without that belief supporting her,)

621
00:38:32,604 --> 00:38:34,264
(she's really going to collapse.)

622
00:38:35,143 --> 00:38:36,583
Congratulations!

623
00:38:36,583 --> 00:38:37,864
Congratulations, Mr. Qin.

624
00:38:37,864 --> 00:38:39,183
Congratulations, Mr. Qin.

625
00:38:41,063 --> 00:38:42,103
Your provincial troupe

626
00:38:42,784 --> 00:38:45,864
ruined the script

627
00:38:45,864 --> 00:38:47,103
I poured everything into.

628
00:38:48,344 --> 00:38:51,264
- Why bring this up now?
- The Qinqiang opera

629
00:38:52,023 --> 00:38:53,784
got turned into Qin songs!

630
00:38:53,784 --> 00:38:55,304
You're drunk, really.

631
00:38:55,304 --> 00:38:55,984
This...

632
00:38:55,984 --> 00:38:57,183
What is this about? You...

633
00:38:57,984 --> 00:38:58,543
Mr. Qin,

634
00:38:59,503 --> 00:39:01,344
whether it's Qinqiang opera
or Qin songs,

635
00:39:01,464 --> 00:39:03,384
we at least won an opera award.

636
00:39:03,384 --> 00:39:04,344
- Right?
- Yeah.

637
00:39:05,623 --> 00:39:07,103
The quality of an opera

638
00:39:08,103 --> 00:39:10,183
can't be decided by one award.

639
00:39:10,543 --> 00:39:11,824
But an award

640
00:39:11,824 --> 00:39:13,464
surely represents

641
00:39:13,464 --> 00:39:16,304
that some aspect of the opera
is outstanding.

642
00:39:16,784 --> 00:39:18,543
Otherwise, why is
the award so sought-after?

643
00:39:18,904 --> 00:39:19,503
Exactly.

644
00:39:19,984 --> 00:39:21,143
I don't seek one.

645
00:39:23,503 --> 00:39:24,344
You don't?

646
00:39:24,824 --> 00:39:25,784
Then I'd like to ask,

647
00:39:26,424 --> 00:39:27,223
who

648
00:39:28,143 --> 00:39:31,703
wrote three full pages
of an acceptance speech

649
00:39:31,703 --> 00:39:33,424
and stayed up all night,

650
00:39:33,703 --> 00:39:35,864
only to lose his voice
from excitement the next day

651
00:39:35,864 --> 00:39:36,904
and couldn't read it?

652
00:39:37,223 --> 00:39:38,744
Who is it?

653
00:39:41,063 --> 00:39:42,623
Why argue about it?

654
00:39:43,063 --> 00:39:45,063
Who enjoys Qinqiang opera these days?

655
00:39:45,063 --> 00:39:46,304
Who even cares?

656
00:39:46,304 --> 00:39:47,183
What do you mean?

657
00:39:47,183 --> 00:39:47,904
Exactly.

658
00:39:47,904 --> 00:39:49,023
Plenty of people enjoy it.

659
00:39:50,103 --> 00:39:51,103
Mr. Qin,

660
00:39:51,103 --> 00:39:53,143
don't let that acceptance speech
go in vain.

661
00:39:53,703 --> 00:39:54,944
Recite it for us here.

662
00:39:56,703 --> 00:39:57,623
Let us know

663
00:39:58,424 --> 00:39:59,464
what you wrote.

664
00:40:00,904 --> 00:40:02,183
People love to say,

665
00:40:02,864 --> 00:40:04,623
"The opera matters most."

666
00:40:05,703 --> 00:40:07,784
But I say it's deceptive nonsense.

667
00:40:08,864 --> 00:40:10,663
No opera

668
00:40:11,503 --> 00:40:13,304
matters more than life.

669
00:40:14,984 --> 00:40:16,784
Life matters most!

670
00:40:19,703 --> 00:40:21,663
I'm about to write a new script

671
00:40:22,583 --> 00:40:24,304
about life.

672
00:40:25,583 --> 00:40:27,784
I'll have Yi Qin'e perform it.

673
00:40:28,744 --> 00:40:30,304
Let's perform it in Beijing!

674
00:40:30,984 --> 00:40:33,784
Let's perform it at the United Nations!

675
00:40:34,864 --> 00:40:37,384
This opera will be called

676
00:40:38,464 --> 00:40:40,344
The Fox Immortal's Whimper.

677
00:40:42,623 --> 00:40:47,904
The Fox Immortal's Whimper!

678
00:40:48,143 --> 00:40:48,736
Good!

679
00:40:48,736 --> 00:40:50,183
- Good!
- Good!

680
00:40:50,183 --> 00:40:57,152
♪The broken cliff edge
holds the waning moon♪

681
00:40:57,984 --> 00:41:00,183
- Good!
- Good!

682
00:41:19,273 --> 00:41:23,608
(Barbecue)

683
00:41:39,183 --> 00:41:39,864
Hua.

684
00:41:43,663 --> 00:41:44,623
Hua.

685
00:41:53,023 --> 00:41:54,103
Hua.

686
00:42:00,384 --> 00:42:01,464
It's so late.

687
00:42:02,503 --> 00:42:03,464
Where has she gone?

688
00:42:10,023 --> 00:42:13,384
I had a bit to drink,
and wanted to tell you something.

689
00:42:18,304 --> 00:42:20,424
I hold it in my heart for half a year.

690
00:42:21,744 --> 00:42:23,784
More than it, almost half a lifetime.

691
00:42:26,784 --> 00:42:28,143
I never said it out loud.

692
00:42:34,503 --> 00:42:36,464
At this age,

693
00:42:36,464 --> 00:42:38,543
without confirming
our relationship clearly,

694
00:42:39,583 --> 00:42:42,143
we've just muddled through like this.

695
00:42:44,384 --> 00:42:47,703
We've muddled through
like this for half a lifetime,

696
00:42:48,583 --> 00:42:51,824
without confirming anything.

697
00:42:52,663 --> 00:42:53,503
That won't work.

698
00:42:54,583 --> 00:42:57,703
Today, I must speak my mind to you.

699
00:42:57,984 --> 00:42:58,824
Well,

700
00:42:59,103 --> 00:43:00,023
the two of us

701
00:43:01,464 --> 00:43:02,503
should get married.

702
00:43:05,120 --> 00:43:06,944
(Preview)

703
00:43:08,824 --> 00:43:12,503
(Dozens of the country's
top pediatric cardiology experts)

704
00:43:12,503 --> 00:43:14,223
(all attended the meeting.)

705
00:43:14,223 --> 00:43:15,464
Please save my child.

706
00:43:15,464 --> 00:43:16,784
The surgery has risks.

707
00:43:17,063 --> 00:43:18,583
Can my kid pull through this?

708
00:43:18,864 --> 00:43:20,703
No matter how, we'll overcome them.

709
00:43:20,944 --> 00:43:22,384
We can't submit to fate.

710
00:43:22,384 --> 00:43:23,703
We have to believe in ourselves.

711
00:43:24,143 --> 00:43:26,264
Driving a taxi doesn't need much skill.

712
00:43:26,264 --> 00:43:27,264
Remember,

713
00:43:27,264 --> 00:43:29,744
get more jobs, drive faster.

714
00:43:29,744 --> 00:43:30,944
I found a new job.

715
00:43:30,944 --> 00:43:33,063
Believe me, we can definitely
cure the kid's illness.

716
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,620
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

717
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:47,930
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

718
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,560
♪We met and brushed past♪

719
00:43:55,120 --> 00:44:02,420
♪Your shadow drifted out of sight♪

720
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:20,540
♪The stove fire blazed in my dream♪

721
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:27,710
♪Lit up the tracks of pearly tears♪

722
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:32,890
♪In my dream, water sleeves flew♪

723
00:44:34,020 --> 00:44:39,610
♪Hiding a lifetime of love♪

724
00:44:40,770 --> 00:44:44,970
♪The Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage♪

725
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:51,640
♪Spring water brewed strong wine♪

726
00:44:52,810 --> 00:44:57,500
♪Sheep moved through the valley♪

727
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:03,350
♪It felt like a promise
from another life♪

728
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:09,050
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

729
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:15,510
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

730
00:45:15,890 --> 00:45:21,170
♪If I chose again, I'd still roam♪

731
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:27,930
♪All over this sunlit plateau♪

732
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:33,350
♪The dream ends; the curtain falls♪

733
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:39,410
♪Moonlight washes off this stage makeup♪

734
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,920
♪The one in the mirror wears gray hair♪

735
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:51,220
♪Already sang all my joy and sorrow♪

736
00:45:52,020 --> 00:46:01,050
♪Already shouted across Qinchuan Plain♪

